author: Lim
text:
Good gym, despite its small size, lots of equipment to get a decent workout done, impressed with all that they were able to squeeze. The entire space feels semi-broken up into 3 sections though. Plenty of cable stations.
Not sure why some folks are complaining about aircon? It is one of the colder AFs I‚Äôve been to, comparable to JTC summit. Visited on a weekday, able to push hard without sweating. Try AFs like Northpoint and you will know what ‚Äòhot‚Äô feels like.
Cons: lots of white collar folks on weekdays, even at odd timings like 3-4pm. Gets more packed at lunchtime and after work, so avoid those hours. Wish there were more benches, theres only 4 minus the one at the smith machine, they were all occupied on a weekday afternoon. Dumbbell racks split into 2 sides which was abit awkward, and only one deadlift platform tucked in the corner right next to a wall. If you do powerlifting, or simply want a more spacious gym, consider other outlets like City Hall (crowd can be quite bad too)
Mirrors are aesthetic lol
Overall nice place, don‚Äôt mind coming on weekends when there is less people.

author: RCK
text:
‚ö†Ô∏è Please be cautious with this gym and sign up at your own risk.

Before referring my friends, I specifically asked the staff (Brock) if I would be entitled to the ‚Äúrefer a friend‚Äù reward of one free month, and he confirmed that I would. Based on that, I referred three friends to sign up.

However, after they joined and I followed up a few months later, I was told that I am not entitled to any referral benefits because my membership is not under the Raffles Place branch. This was completely different from what I was assured earlier.

Not only did I not receive the promised free month, but my friends also did not receive any referral gifts. This change of information after sign-up feels misleading and unprofessional. I hope the management will review this matter seriously and ensure that terms are communicated clearly and honoured consistently moving forward.

‚ö†Ô∏è Please be cautious with this gym and sign up at your own risk.

author: En88 Lin
text:
Disappointing Experience with Referral Program
When I first considered referring my friends, I checked with a staff member (Brock) and was told clearly that I would receive one month free for each successful referral. Trusting that information, I introduced three friends to sign up.

Only months later, when I followed up, I was told that I was not entitled to any rewards because my membership is not under the Raffles Place branch. This was never mentioned at the start, and it completely contradicted what I was told.

In the end, neither I nor my friends received the promised rewards. The whole experience left me feeling misled and disappointed.
‚ö†Ô∏è I would advise anyone considering this gym to clarify everything in writing before signing up.

text:
Amazing gym and team, but BEWARE this outlet becomes an extremely hostile environment during the weekday hours of 6:00 to 8:30 AM, M-Fri, entirely due to the presence of a nasty & entitled female bully with the worst gym etiquette. She monopolizes multiple pieces of equipment all at the same time, including the only Smith machine, the leg press, and additional kits‚Äî doing insane number of sets for an excessive two-hour period without the willingness to share, giving you big time attitude for it. She also lashes out at other women, scolding them for being 'in her way,' even when she's clearly the one at fault. At the same time slamming weights and grunting excessively.

Worse still, this member secretly films other members without their knowledge or consent followed by posting these videos publicly on her page to ridicule, demean and humiliate them for her own personal gratification. Verbally abusing women in person and on her page. Even doxxing fellow members, exposing their private information online.

Outside of this toxic time slot, when this individual is absent, the gym is an outstanding facility with excellent management and a supportive community. The trainers are especially friendly, conscientious and helpful. They go out of their way to do a great job, one of the best AF trainers I've seen.

text:
Newly opened AF outlet with brand new, super smooth equipment. The outlet is also really clean. The space is definitely a little bit small, especially the bathroom area and the functional workout area. The number of stalls available is quite limited, although they generally tend to be quite clean.

As with any new outlet with good equipment, it is extremely crowded particularly during lunchtime. Given the limited space of the outlet, you can definitely feel the crowd, but that's not really something they can help though. I have to say for the limited amount of space they have, there is a decent number of equipment available. Would give this 5/5 stars if it wasn't so crowded all the time, but hey - it's only crowded because it's a good gym.

author: Melvin
text:
The only redeeming factor about this place is the location. That's really it.

The place is hot, ventilation is minimal as mentioned by other reviews. Running on the treadmills during the evening peak hour is comparable, or even worse, than running outdoors in terms of heat and humidity.

Recently, apparently due to complaints from neighbouring offices regarding noise, they've padded the rack pins used to hold the bars. This makes the bar 'stick' to the pin, making it a little harder to unrack the bar. It also makes it hard to adjust the bar's position when racked - So if I put a slightly heavier weight and cant adjust it, I've got to unload all the weights, adjust the bar, and then load the weights back on. This might be a little niche, but its very inconvenient. Also strangely enough, there seems to be no issue with the noise from the deadlift platform?

The worst part of it all? Their responses to the feedbacks given. No matter how many times I've raised the issue regarding the gym being hot and humid for example, 10/10 times I'm told that there's nothing that can be done and to just suck it up. I've read some of the responses here saying that they'd do something about the heat, but given that I've raised this since I first came to the gym and there's been no change at all, I doubt anything is going to happen honestly.

text:
Fantastic experience at Anytime Fitness! The staff here are very friendly and always make you feel welcome. The gym is clean with a great variety of equipment. The overall vibe is very good ‚Äî positive and motivating.

Special shoutout to Irfan for being so helpful and approachable! Thanks for creating such a great atmosphere.

Editing my review as at September 2025:

I originally had good experience with the staff when I signed up at the start of the year. But seems like the staff I was in contact with has left and now the service and management has been lacklustre.

I‚Äôve had to freeze my account due to injury and they have constantly been charging me extra / being inaccurate with the amounts that I‚Äôve had to continuously clarify with them and even calculate the amounts on my own to tell them.

After noticing their mistake of charging me extra, not only did I not receive any apology after pointing it out, I was also met with condescension when I gave my feedback in hopes they will improve in future as well as for other customers.
